Insider Activity


Individual




Laurence E. Hirsch



Mr. Laurence E. Hirsch is Independent Director at Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp., Chairman at Highlander Partners LP, Chairman at Eagle Materials, Inc., and Chairman at Center for European Policy Analysis. He is on the Board of Directors at Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. and University of Pennsylvania.
Mr. Hirsch co-founded Highlander Partners in April 2004 after he retired from the position of CEO and Chairman of the Board of Centex Corporation, one of the largest homebuilding and related financial services companies in the U.S at that time (in 2009 Centex was acquired by Pulte Homes Inc.). Mr. Hirsch had served as Centex’s CEO since 1988 and as Chairman since 1991. He joined the company in 1985 as President, COO and a Board member.
Prior to Centex, Mr. Hirsch served as President, CEO, and a director of Southdown, Inc., a cement and oil and gas producer. He successfully transformed Southdown, Inc. from a struggling conglomerate into the country’s premier domestically-owned cement producer, which was later acquired by Cemex, S.A. de C.V. Prior to that, he was a partner at Bracewell and Patterson, a Houston-based law firm.
Currently, Mr. Hirsch also serves on the boards of directors of A. H. Belo Corporation, a newspaper publishing company, and an Advisory Director of the Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International Studies.
Mr. Hirsch holds a BS in Economics from The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania as well as a JD, cum laude, from the Villanova University School of Law and a Masters Degree in International Public Policy from Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International Studies. He received the Bene Merito award from the government of Poland in 2010.



