Executive Profile
Laurence E. Hirsch J.D.Co-Founder and Chairman, Highlander Partners, L.P.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. Laurence E. Hirsch, J.D., also known as Larry, serves as a Co-Founder of Highlander Partners, L.P and serves as its Chairman since April 2004. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of CXP since April 1, 2003. Mr. Hirsch served as the Chief Executive Officer of Centex Corporation from 1988 July to March 31, 2004 and its President from March 1985 to July 1991. He has been the Chairman of Eagle Materials Inc. (formerly Centex Construction Products Inc.) since July ... 1999. He serves as the Chairman of the Board at Center for European Policy Analysis. He has been a Director at Eagle Materials Inc. since 1985. Mr. Hirsch serves as a Director of Commercial Metals Company. He serves as an Advisory Director at Heidelberger Zement AG. He serves as a Trustee of BlackRock Investors, Inc. He served as a Trustee of University of Pennsylvania. He served as the Chairman of the Board at Centex Corporation from 1991 July to March 31, 2004 and CXP board from January 1994 to December 1997 and since July 1999. He served as a Director of Freddie Mac since December 18, 2008, A. H. Belo Corporation from December 2007 to May 18, 2011, Centex Corporation Director from 1985 to March 31, 2004, ENVOY Corporation since February 1995, Old Envoy from 1987 to June 6, 1995, Luminex Corporation from December 1996 to March 17, 2005, Belo Corp. from August 1999 to January 2008 and Cavco Industries Inc. He served as a Member of Advisory Council at HeidelbergCement AG. Mr. Hirsch received a B.S. in Economics from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania and a J.D. from the Villanova University School of Law.Read Full Background




